FBIS4-3221 "drchi075_p_94005" FBIS-CHI-94-075 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 Central-South Region Shenzhen Machinery, Electronics Export Fair Opens Shenzhen Machinery, Electronics Export Fair Opens OW1804142894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1245 GMT 18 Apr 94 OW1804142894 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Shenzhen, April 18 (XINHUA) -- An export fair of machinery and electronic products opened here today, with 400 manufacturers from all over China attending. Overseas firms can order machine tools, general-purpose machines, food packing machines, motor vehicles and parts, printing machines, aviation equipment, farm machinery, meters and instruments and electronics products on display during the fair, the largest of its kind in China. Government statistics show that China's exports of machinery and electric products soared to 22.7 billion U.S. dollars in 1993 as against 1.68 billion dollars in 1986, rising at an annual rate of 21 percent. These products accounted for nearly 25 percent of China's exports in 1993, up 19 percentage points from 1985.
